data.description: Welcome Home! This 3-bedroom, 3-bathroom home has been freshly painted inside and has brand new carpet and padding throughout. The kitchen features a unique backsplash and it opens to the dining room and family room. The dining room leads to the backyard through a brand new sliding glass door. The family room and the living room are separated by the 2-sided gas log fireplace beneath the vaulted ceiling. All three bedrooms can be found on the upper floor. The master suite includes a walk in closet with built-in shelving and the bathroom has a large bathtub. The freshly painted basement has large egress windows that provide ample natural light along with a closet should you choose to use it as a conforming 4th bedroom. The washer and dryer can be found in the utility room in the basement. And if you are wondering about the utilities, this house has solar panels that reduce your costs greatly. The backyard also has a brand new deck, perfect for BBQ. Nestled at the end of a cul-de-sac within a quiet Castle Rock neighborhood. You will find friendly neighbors, top-rated schools, and easy access to shopping and dining options. With scenic parks, hiking trails, and Castlewood Canyon State Park nearby, outdoor enthusiasts will delight in the countless recreational opportunities.
